{
  "texts": [
    "Although (14) is typically intractable, it can be sampled using MCMC, and the parameter samples retained to give (dependent) draws from π enkf,T (θ|y 0:T), the θ-marginal of (14).",
    "The resulting approach, termed ensemble MCMC (eMCMC) is detailed in Drovandi et al. (2022) (see also Stroud et al., 2018; Katzfuss et al., 2019).",
    "In brief, at iteration k, a new θ * is proposed from a kernel q(θ k-1, •).",
    "Then, sampling of the corresponding ensemble {x *,1:N 0:T, x *,1:N 0:T } from ψ",
    "T (•, •) and evaluation of the observed data likelihood p (θ *) enkf,T (y 0:T |x *,1:N 0:T), is achieved through recursive application of Algorithm 3."
  ]
}